messages.subject: Joylyn
messages.messageBody:
<<
Lexie heard the song "we don't need no education, we don't need no
thought control..." today. What is that song called? The wall?

anyway, she thought it was a really cool song!

I can just hear her singing that now.>>

Hi Joylyn,

I'm sure twentyhundred people will respond, but I'm gonna too! :)
That's "Another Brick in the Wall" by Pink Floyd, though it was remade
in the last several years for a movie (The Faculty maybe?) I dunno. I
remember singing this on the bus in high school... It was a fairly new
song back then... Ugh I'm old. LOL...

~Alyce
